q
.058824 .098039 .137255 rg
BT 1 0 0 1 0 54.5 Tm /F1 9.5 Tf 16 TL 2.57636 Tw (As these systems acquire consequential authority over human affairs, the question of where authority) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.845273 Tw (resides, how it is established, and when it must be treated as having ended is no longer optional. It is) Tj T* 0 Tw .060866 Tw (structural. A system that can affect lives must be able to demonstrate that it was authorised to do so \227 not in) Tj T* 0 Tw (general, not historically, but at the exact moment the action occurred.) Tj T* ET
Q
Q
q
1 0 0 1 68.3622 440.4417 cm
q
.058824 .098039 .137255 rg
BT 1 0 0 1 0 70.5 Tm /F1 9.5 Tf 16 TL .416057 Tw (Existing governance frameworks address behaviour. They focus on fairness, bias, safety, and transparency.) Tj T* 0 Tw .043893 Tw (These are legitimate and necessary concerns. But they do not define the most critical condition: when does a) Tj T* 0 Tw .507012 Tw (system have the right to act? Without that definition, systems continue operating after the human conditions) Tj T* 0 Tw .011773 Tw (that justified their operation have changed or no longer exist. The system is still acting \227 but no longer acting) Tj T* 0 Tw (under valid authority.) Tj T* ET
Q
Q
q
1 0 0 1 68.3622 381.1031 cm
q
.058824 .098039 .137255 rg
BT 1 0 0 1 0 38.5 Tm /F1 9.5 Tf 16 TL .338653 Tw (This is not a rare failure. It is not an edge case. It is not a system defect. It is the default condition of current) Tj T* 0 Tw .014574 Tw (systems operating at scale \227 because authority has never been explicitly defined as a requirement that must) Tj T* 0 Tw (be satisfied at execution.) Tj T* ET
Q
