BT 1 0 0 1 0 54.5 Tm /F1 9.5 Tf 16 TL .487913 Tw (AI systems have been given the ability to act before we defined what gives them the right to act. This is the) Tj T* 0 Tw .431263 Tw (root issue. Capability has advanced faster than the governance frameworks needed to constrain it. Systems) Tj T* 0 Tw 4.200129 Tw (have been deployed with the power to make consequential decisions without any requirement to) Tj T* 0 Tw (demonstrate, at the moment of each decision, that they are authorised to make it.) Tj T* ET
Q
Q
q
1 0 0 1 68.3622 491.111 cm
q
.058824 .098039 .137255 rg
BT 1 0 0 1 0 70.5 Tm /F1 9.5 Tf 16 TL 1.526477 Tw (Authority has been implied, assumed, or inherited from system access, rather than explicitly defined and) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.660569 Tw (maintained. A system is granted access, and access is treated as though it were authority. A system is) Tj T* 0 Tw .685871 Tw (deployed with a purpose, and that purpose is treated as though it were a continuous mandate. A system is) Tj T* 0 Tw 2.453105 Tw (authenticated at the start of a session, and that authentication is treated as though it validated every) Tj T* 0 Tw (subsequent action.) Tj T* ET
Q
Q
q
1 0 0 1 68.3622 415.7724 cm
q
.058824 .098039 .137255 rg
BT 1 0 0 1 0 54.5 Tm /F1 9.5 Tf 16 TL .670959 Tw (This creates a gap between who a system appears to act for and whether it is actually authorised to act. A) Tj T* 0 Tw .262545 Tw (system can appear legitimate while operating without legitimate authority. That is the failure condition \227 and) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.18054 Tw (it is a condition that persists silently, because nothing in the system's normal operation signals that it has) Tj T* 0 Tw (been crossed.) Tj T* ET
Q
Q
q
1 0 0 1 68.3622 340.4339 cm
q
.058824 .098039 .137255 rg
BT 1 0 0 1 0 54.5 Tm /F1 9.5 Tf 16 TL .167299 Tw (This gap is not visible during normal operation. Systems continue functioning. Outputs are produced. Actions) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.071945 Tw (occur. Nothing looks broken. But legitimacy is not determined by appearance. It is determined by whether) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.348187 Tw (authority exists at the moment of action. When that condition is not enforced, systems do not stop. They) Tj T* 0 Tw (continue. And that continuation is where unauthorised action begins.) Tj T* ET
Q
Q
q
1 0 0 1 68.3622 265.0953 cm
q
.058824 .098039 .137255 rg
BT 1 0 0 1 0 54.5 Tm /F1 9.5 Tf 16 TL .074628 Tw (This is why the problem persists unnoticed. Systems are judged by output, not by authority. And output alone) Tj T* 0 Tw .181629 Tw (cannot confirm legitimacy. A system can produce correct-looking outputs under invalid authority. The outputs) Tj T* 0 Tw .196434 Tw (do not reveal the failure. Only the authority record does \227 and in most systems, no such record exists at the) Tj T* 0 Tw (moment of action.) Tj T* ET
Q
Q
q
1 0 0 1 68.3622 141.7567 cm
q
.058824 .098039 .137255 rg
BT 1 0 0 1 0 102.5 Tm /F1 9.5 Tf 16 TL 1.035899 Tw (The sequence of development in modern systems has prioritised capability over legitimacy. Systems have) Tj T* 0 Tw .260552 Tw (been designed to optimise performance, efficiency, and scale before establishing the conditions under which) Tj T* 0 Tw 5.565848 Tw (their actions are permitted. This inversion creates a structural imbalance. In traditional human) Tj T* 0 Tw 2.416322 Tw (decision-making environments, authority is inherently linked to accountability. A decision is made by a) Tj T* 0 Tw 3.187682 Tw (person, at a specific moment, under identifiable conditions. Responsibility is traceable. In automated) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.691432 Tw (environments, that linkage is weakened. Systems operate continuously, often without a discrete moment) Tj T* 0 Tw (where authority is re-established.) Tj T* ET
Q
Q
q
1 0 0 1 68.3622 98.41811 cm
q
.058824 .098039 .137255 rg
BT 1 0 0 1 0 22.5 Tm /F1 9.5 Tf 16 TL .482677 Tw (The absence of this re-establishment is not treated as a failure within current system design. It is treated as) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.213812 Tw (normal operation. This creates a condition where actions are derived from prior states rather than current) Tj T* 0 Tw ET
Q
Q
 

